# ── OneIBC BOD Dashboard — environment variables ──────────────────────────
# Copy to .env.local (dev) or set in Railway → Variables (prod).
# All are OPTIONAL: with none set, the app serves the static seed data.

# Data-source priority: Google Sheets → CSV URL → static seed.

# 1) Google Sheets (recommended). The spreadsheet ID (between /d/ and /edit).
#    Sheet must be shared "Anyone with the link → Viewer" or Published to web.
# GOOGLE_SHEET_ID=

# Optional: private sheets via a service account (full JSON on one line).
#    When set, the Sheets API v4 is used instead of the public CSV export.
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY=
# GOOGLE_SHEET_TAB=Sheet1

# 2) CSV URL (alternative to Google Sheets).
# DASHBOARD_CSV_URL=https://your-domain.com/data.csv

# Note: Railway provides PORT automatically; `next start` reads it. No need to set it.
